# Release Packaging Rule

## Release artifacts
- Source files in repository:
  - `install-switch-env.sh`
  - `switch-env`
  - `switch-env.plugin.zsh`
- Built installer:
  - `switch-env-installer.sh`

## Build policy
- Build installer from repository root only.
- Keep README install instructions aligned with actual build/install commands.

## Distribution policy
- Prefer `raw.githubusercontent.com` installer URL after push.
- Support local installer execution for offline distribution.

## Shebang policy
- Source file `switch-env` should keep portable shebang (`/usr/bin/env python3`).
- Installer can rewrite runtime shebang for installed target in `~/bin`.
